<font color="#FF0000">GUILTY AS CHARGED</font><br>
<tt>Thu Oct 23 21:33:20 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Arthur, bravo for your post, even if it gave me a headache too. Cook, what can I say, you do your homework very well. The protestors who did the stunt with the trains in Oakland were not me.  I admit I exagerated in the heat of bait and rebate (is that a coupon?), I never was part of SDS (Students for a Democratic Society-Oakland Branch), but I was in the Long Beach Chapter,  and I thought I was writing in the collective &quot;we&quot;. Yeah, on re-reading it, it looks lame and I look guilty as charged. Sorry bout that. So what. You guys did a helluva job correcting me and I accept your twenty wacks.<br><br>
I did a &quot;symbolic&quot; train track stunt once in Long Beach, and felt totally like a fool for doing it. The railroad was going into the harbor and supposedly carrying bombs to ship to Nam.  Please Arthur, my mind, or what is left of it, is spinning.  I can not stand up to this torture, I will say anything you want. Did I shot JFK? Yes. Am I really Oliver Stoned? Of course. Am I a jungle boat captain on LSD, Obviously.Yes, Yes, Oh GOD, Yes. Anything, Yes.<br><br>
I think I share with all of you, that late at night the heat of the moment gets the fingers moving faster then the brain is thinking, and I admit that Arthur and Cook are right, I never did the Oakland train stunt.  They are to be congradulated for exposing me, for whatever that is worth.<br><br>
That does not change the fact, or the time of the post Art, that someone else has been posting in my name.  I think that is sort of chickenshit, and I wish whoever is doing it, KEEP IT UP. I love it. Makes me question my sanity, which I know is slippin since I joined this site.  So, to my alter ego, other personality, or imposter, please continue. Maybe I can end up drawing benefits too, down the line, and get on some grooovy drug, like Thorazine or Prolixen, and not have a care in the world.  Again, to my two most severe critics, Art and Cook, you nailed me good. Now what? Have either of you ever &quot;embellished&quot; something for effect?
